values:
Tell 20 things about you that others might not know then tag 6 others to do it.

1.God is my best friend.
2.I love tattoos,i have 3 already,although i'm not letting myself get n-e more'cause i believe tats are really against God's will.
3.I promised myself that im not dating until i meet someone who i can potentially marry.
4.I got baptized when i was 14.
5.I have big feet.
6.I can't stand letting my hair grow longer than about 2 inches.
7.Tetris is by far the greatest game i have ever played.
8.I write to relieve stress.
9.I love to rollerblade but very much dislike ice-skateing.
10.When i was in 4th grade my little bro threw me down the stairs & i broke my arm.
11.I got my first tattoo on December 8,1999 i was 12.
12.I want to be like my mom when i grow up.
13.I'm lactose intolerant,but love dairy.
14.I wish i was still a virgin.
15.I love photographing clouds.
16.I enjoy cleaning,sweeping in particular.
17.I drink entirely too much coffee.
18.For some reason i dislike digital photography.
19.I haven't gotten to see the Northern Lights yet here in Alaska.
20.I hate mushy movies but secretly wish that stuff was real.


OOps...I dont have 6 friends on LJ,so i cant tag n-e one.I guess I lose.

Lots of new things happening.For one,I'm in FAIRBANKS,ALASKA on vacation w/my sis.Its cool, but can't wait to go home.I miss my mommy:)My church, Sunlight Community Church finally found a youth minister and we're starting a youth group,it should be fun.I'm glad I came on this trip it makes me appreciate my family and home alot more.But no matter where i am i can always feel GOD right next to me, thats awesome.Well GOD is faithful,I've been choosing GOD's will over my own for a while now and i feel like HE is blessing me for it.I still feel lonely at times but i know that if i wait for the man GOD chose for me that all will be well.

Just when you think that you are letting yourself slip away God strengthens you and lifts you up. How can we help others believe in God? It seems like people are scared to know God in a personal way. Maybe because they know that when they come to know Him they will truly see how unworthy they are of God's love.
Maybe then they will feel like they should change their ways, and that can be very scary.

Its been a while...so anyway God is good as usual, hes better than good , hes so wonderful i am in awe of Him. But why do i still feel the longings for someone?Someone to spend the rest of my life with. I am happy with my life but my heart still aches for a love that might not even exist, a romantic love that ive only dreamt of. Gods love is the greatest love and i truly know and feel that, Hes the one that fills me to the core with peace and love and every great emotion ive ever experienced.So how can i feel so complete and yet still incomplete?

Brothers and sisters happy Good Friday! Good Friday is one of the very best celebrations in the entire year! Because Jesus sacrificed himself for us, we can live in peace and in joy. Jesus Christ...my everything. It was almost impossible to feel loneliness and sadness today because of thinking about how much love God has for me. Uhhh...how great. Give thanks to the Lord, and remember the true meaning of Easter. He rose! He is the messiah! Why do people make Easter about bunnies, colored eggs, and choclates?!

" Whereas you do not know what will happen tomorrow. For what is your life? It is even a vapor that appears for a little time and then vanishes away. "
                                                         - James 4:14

Tomorrow isnt promised to us, life is really short.
Now is the time to save lives , now is the time to witness and feed the starving children. When will we 
give everything away and follow Christ? When will we love like Jesus told us to? When? Will we loose our lives to save them? When will we choose others well beings rather than our own? When will we stop the selfishness and realize we have too much and so many dont have enough? Will we take on the mission, and fulfill our purposes in this life? Every day countless unsaved souls die, how sad, everyday the population in hell grows. I have loved ones that aren't saved, to think of their suffering after this life, its heart wrenching.I pray ... for the courage to get involved, to have the right words to say.I pray ... that God would open their hearts to Him.

" Have i not commanded you? Be strong and of good courage; do not be afraid, nor be dismayed, for the Lord your God is with you wherever you go. "         - Joshua 1:9

God has plans for us, He wants to use us, it is not our lives that we are living, it is His that He mercifully gave to us.
My morning prayer is that i live for God throughout my day. And i see that He is using me.
God was there at the Tree 63 show last night, as we gathered to praise Him. And He wanted to use me, to sponsor a child in need through WorldVision.
I will go wherever He wants me to, i will do what He asks, because He will be with me WHEREVER I GO.
So I will be strong and of good courage.

" For i know the thoughts that I think toward you, says the Lord, thoughts of peace and not of evil, to give you a future and a hope. "
                                                                - Jeremiah 29:11

God has great plans for us, He wants to give us peace and a future of hope. Isn't that awesome that we don't need to worry because God has everything in control?
He alone is worthy of all the glory and praises, from every mouth in every nation.

My mom is the best hairstylist, she gave me my Hawk back! Sweet!
Anyway, cool day, i was reading my "Today" booklet and the author wrote some cool stuff:
"Jesus is the sun that melts the ice of a frozen heart.
Jesus is the artist who sees a masterpiece in a block of limestone.
He sees the person God created you to be, and he draws that forth with the force of his transforming love."

We can do the impossible, we can change the inalterable, if we only have patience and trust in God to bring about His good will in His own time. I used to become so impatient with myself day after day when i would try to break a bad habit but kept disappointing myself, but before i knew it the sin was no longer a constant in my life; God took it away, im changing like ive always wanted. In the past year, the sins i wanted to get rid of are dying off one by one and its only through God thats its possible to stay that way. But i realize now that changing your life completely around takes time, your heart takes time to heal from letting go of your old ways, and God is making you a new creation. It feels great to feel God holding your hand everyday.

You're everything i've ever wanted
You're the love i've been searching for 
I was looking in all the wrong places
But now i've found you Lord
I feel safe in You, so blessed to know You
No one else can compare
They think they know love, but they haven't found You
You gave me peace, You wiped my tears, i dont cry like before
You healed my broken heart, it doesnt bleed anymore
You opened my eyes, and now i see far more
Father your everything ive ever wanted
I feel safe in You Lord
